[[Professor/Legends|Professor]] '''H. Hrush''' was an individual who was the [[Author/Legends|author]] of a [[Book/Legends|book]] entitled ''[[The Lost Twenty: Dooku's Rise]]'', though it was published without consent from the proper parties. The book concerned a [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] named [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]],<ref name="News">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|45||A Closer Look}}</ref> who [[Lost Twenty/Legends|resigned]] from the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] to found a [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|militarized confederacy]] of [[Planet/Legends|worlds]] that wished to secede from the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="The New Essential Chronology">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> For a [[Time/Legends|time]], Hrush's book was listed as the number-two best-selling book on a list compiled by [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]] on the [[Great ReSynchronization|date]] [[23 BBY/Legends|13:2:28]].<ref name="News" />

==Behind the scenes==
H. Hrush was mentioned in [[HoloNet News Vol. 531 45|''HoloNet News Vol. 531 #45'']], a<ref name="News" /> [[2002]]<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=threads/5990764|board=Literature|thread=The Official HoloNetNews Discussion Thread|archiveurl=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/dY0zn}}</ref> [[in-universe]] [[HoloNet News (original website)|website]].<ref name="News" /> The website's content was written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Paul Ens]].<ref name="HoloNet">{{HoloNetNewsWeb||credits.html|Credits}}</ref>

